    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-09T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/242</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-09T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 11, 1.45 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3313. For War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1"
                        >Dresel</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 27. My No. 16, April 28.<note n="2" xml:id="d662fn2">Not printed; the
                        principal terms of the cotton agreement as signed are given in the
                        Minister’s telegram No. 2929, Mar. 24, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_1605">p. 1605</ref>.</note> New cotton agreement was signed
                    May 8 without change from terms stated. Letter stating no American cotton will
                    be exported any form to Central Powers will be delivered immediately. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
